In [243]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt #     

# your code here
df = pd.read_csv("youtube_trending_mediterranean.csv")
df['publishedAt'] = pd.to_datetime(df['publishedAt']).dt.date
df_unique_videos = df.drop_duplicates(subset='video_id')
videos_per_date = df_unique_videos.groupby('publishedAt').size()

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
videos_per_date.plot(kind='line', marker='o', color='g')
plt.title('      ', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel(' ', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel(' ', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True)
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

# your code here
df = pd.read_csv("youtube_trending_mediterranean.csv")
videos_per_country = df['country'].value_counts().sort_index()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
videos_per_country.plot(kind='bar', color='orange')

plt.title('    ', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel(' ', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.xticks(rotation=0, ha='center')
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

# your code here
df = pd.read_csv("youtube_trending_mediterranean.csv")
france_videos = df[(df['country'] == 'FR') & (df['comments_disabled'] == False)]
view_counts = france_videos['view_count']
comment_counts = france_videos['comment_count']

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.scatter(view_counts, comment_counts, alpha=0.6, color='orange')
plt.title('      ()', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel(' ', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel(' ', fontsize=12)
plt.xscale("log")
plt.yscale("log")
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()
